title: For Sale:  Winchester 1897
postcontent: I have a Winchester Model 1897 up for sale. I've done a lot of digging on this shotgun, and here's what I know: It was manufactured in 1911, it's in the first generation of the "last" 1897s made. I.e. this model is the final product, Winchester made no improvements or tweaks to this line of shotguns from the time this one was made till they ended production in 1957. It has a 30" barrel and 5 round tube. In the 104 years this shotgun has been around it has less then 700 rounds through it. My great grandfather kept it hanging on his wall, took it down to clean it, and on rare occasion hunt with it (He preferred using his 1887.). Everything about this 1897 is all original. i'm asking 700, price is slightly negotiable.
